column4: "full_text": "Proud to share our final committee assignment \u2013 I\u2019ll be serving on the House Agriculture Committee allowing me to focus on one of the most vital pieces of our economy in #CA10. Ready to get to work for our farmers.\n\nhttps://t.co/u6LYX7epiS"
column29: "description": "Turlock guy. Modesto High grad. Pam\u2019s husband. Foster dog dad. Proudly serving the Central Valley in Congress."

column4: "full_text": "The CA wildfires were devastating. Today we worked across the aisle and won an additional $1.9 billion to help farmers rebuild. We have lots more to do
column5: but this is a start.\n\nIf you were effected by the wildfires call my office at (209) 579 5458 and we can help. https://t.co/u8SLnrTXld"
column80: "description": "Turlock guy. Modesto High grad. Pam\u2019s husband. Foster dog dad. Proudly serving the Central Valley in Congress."

column4: "full_text": "Thrilled to be on the House Ed & Labor Committee (and still TBD others). I ran to make a difference on issues that matter to  #CA10\u2014 good jobs
column5: worker's healthcare and setting up the next generation for success. This gives us the voice to do just that.\n\nhttps://t.co/Wgv8BpSs4B"
column30: "description": "Turlock guy. Modesto High grad. Pam\u2019s husband. Foster dog dad. Proudly serving the Central Valley in Congress."

column4: "full_text": "Our communities need this disaster recovery funding. I refuse to let it be taken from us. We have to put politics aside and have a real debate about how we properly secure the border.\n\nhttps://t.co/p0w7MxyPZb"
column27: "description": "Turlock guy. Modesto High grad. Pam\u2019s husband. Foster dog dad. Proudly serving the Central Valley in Congress."

column4: "full_text": "Yesterday for the first time I addressed Congress. I rose to speak because this government shutdown is directly hurting the Central Valley and it needs to stop. You can watch my first speech below. https://t.co/fuTmXAO4LC"
column79: "description": "Turlock guy. Modesto High grad. Pam\u2019s husband. Foster dog dad. Proudly serving the Central Valley in Congress."

column4: "full_text": "This is what is wrong with partisan politics. \n\nImmigration reform is needed
column5: border security is needed. \n\nBut we absolutely shouldn\u2019t shut down the government because we can\u2019t work together. Open the government and stop hurting families who need our government\u2019s help."
column24: "description": "Turlock guy. Modesto High grad. Pam\u2019s husband. Foster dog dad. Proudly serving the Central Valley in Congress."

column4: "full_text": "Congrats to all our @SJGov and @StanCounty representatives who took the oath of office yesterday! Excited to work with you to make life better in the Central Valley!\n\nhttps://t.co/CcvYrUcp3n"
column38: "description": "Turlock guy. Modesto High grad. Pam\u2019s husband. Foster dog dad. Proudly serving the Central Valley in Congress."

column4: "full_text": "31
column5: 000 families in my district are at risk of losing SNAP benefits to feed their kids because of this shutdown. It\u2019s completely unacceptable that our working families are treated like political pawns. It's time we #EndTheShutdown immediately.\n\nhttps://t.co/ushShlNMje"
column30: "description": "Turlock guy. Modesto High grad. Pam\u2019s husband. Foster dog dad. Proudly serving the Central Valley in Congress."

column4: "full_text": "Today
column5: I signed on as a co-sponsor to H.R. 1
column6: the For the People Act. There are a lot of issues we need to tackle in the new Congress
column7: but the corrupting influence of big money in politics is the biggest obstacle to getting things done. Read my Op-Ed.\n\nhttps://t.co/0DkNfE5AIp"
